cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about cross-lingual transfer in natural language processing, specifically in dependency parsing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a hypothesis about the effectiveness of different neural network architectures, which could be considered cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of self-attentive models, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing, and could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models on different languages, which could be considered cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since language is a form of visual data.
